Exercise 3:
    Linking stylesheets to HTML page.
    Explanation on clean HTML and separation between styling and structure.
    Tags reference: href, type, rel
example:
<link href="/style.css" type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" />

Fonts:
The font specified in a stylesheet must be installed on a user's computer in order for that font to display when a user visit the web page. 

font-size: 16 px default.

Serif and Sans-Serif

line-height - interesting concept (Space between lines) - ease the reading. Default maybe 1.5 em.

word-spacing - space between words: 0.3em default (not common).

letter-spacing - Space between words! (kerning) (not common).

font-weight - bold, italic (style of the text).
font-style - same as weight but for italic.
text-transform - Uppercase / Lowercase

text-align - align the side on which the text will stay
